# .env.example — committed template of the environment variables this project needs.
# Copy to `.env` (which is git-ignored) and fill in real values. NEVER commit `.env`.
# Add a line here for every variable your stack/app requires, with a safe placeholder.

# EXAMPLE (replace with your real variables once a stack is chosen):
# DATABASE_URL=postgres://user:password@localhost:5432/dbname
# API_KEY=replace-me
